Members of Kano State House of Assembly have begun the search for a new speaker that will man the affairs of the legislative arm of government for four years. Daily Trust reliably gathered that some potential candidates for the job had started making underground moves to secure the seat. A member of the house, who preferred anonymity, confided in Daily Trust that the seat zoned for Kano south had attracted the attention of some lawmakers from the zone who had started making frantic efforts to secure it. The lawmaker said the choice of next speaker would be easy because some of the lawmakers that were perceived to be the most influential did not return. He expressed optimism that the lawmakers would use their wisdom and experience to elect a competent personality that would bring vibrancy to the assembly. Search for new Kano Speaker begins 2019: How A/Ibom Assembly became a battlefield More lawmakers-elect eye  N/Assembly leadership positions